  "subject": "docs: runbook + README updates for the full Plan-3 surface",
  "body": "- README: component table covering the whole platform surface as of\n  v0.3.0 (ArgoCD, CloudNativePG, ESO, kube-prometheus-stack, MinIO,\n  Lakekeeper, Argo Workflows, Trino, chart/, alice-ingest, the DuckDB\n  extraction tool) -- this repo had no such table before.\n- ingestion-pipeline.md: architecture diagram + a new \"query layer\"\n  paragraph documenting Trino, lake.contract views, apply-views (and that\n  it's manual-only, not scheduled), and the freshness/maintenance Trino\n  steps; env-var table gains FRESHNESS_MAX_AGE_HOURS (the one entry Task\n  3's fixer hadn't added -- TRINO_MAINTENANCE_RETENTION_THRESHOLD was\n  already there); subcommand list gains apply-views, check-freshness,\n  run-trino-maintenance (previously undocumented).\n- backfill.md: Task 3 review residual Minor -- the tandem-raise\n  paragraph's lead-in sentence had the TRINO_MAINTENANCE_RETENTION_\n  THRESHOLD/MAINTENANCE_OLDER_THAN_DAYS scope backwards (claimed the env\n  var touches MAINTENANCE_OLDER_THAN_DAYS, then the very next sentence\n  said the opposite); corrected to match maintenance.py's actual\n  behavior (the env var is Trino-side only).\n- maintenance.py: Task 3 review residual Minor -- one-paragraph docstring\n  note that the nightly-overlap guard only sees CronWorkflow-labeled\n  Workflows (the workflows.argoproj.io/cron-workflow label Argo attaches\n  to scheduled runs only), so a manually kubectl-created ingest Workflow\n  (e.g. hack/run-ingest-once.sh) is invisible to it and won't defer a\n  concurrent manual maintenance trigger -- accepted, the operator running\n  both by hand already owns that window.\n"
